cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically semantic role labeling (SRL), which falls under the scope of cs.CL.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a neural network model for SRL using graph convolutional networks (GCNs), which is a recent class of neural networks.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper is about developing a model for a specific NLP task using machine learning techniques.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper proposes a neural network model, but it is less likely than cs.LG as the focus is on NLP rather than general neural network research.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention any visual data or computer vision tasks, but it is still possible as GCNs have been used in computer vision research as well.
